info.description: A list of openAPIs supported by Aquera for ADP Workforce Now

externalDocs.description: Learn more about the ADP API

get.description: Get list of events based on pagination parameters.

parameters.name: startIndex
parameters.description: The 1-based index of the first query result. Default: 1

parameters.name: count
parameters.description: Non-negative integer. Specified the desired maximum number of query results per page, e.g.: 10. Default: 1000

parameters.name: filter
parameters.description: It supports SCIM filter. For example, type eq "worker.terminate". For more reference to Events filter, follow this Aquera Configuration Guide https://support.aquera.com/hc/en-us/articles/360017945933-ADP-Workforce-Now-Configuration-Guide#h_01G10Q9Y7PM7YYMHGNZXEE1N5C

200.description: Response structure of a single event object

get.description: Fetch an event based on event id

listItems.description: The list of template name and code.

get.description: Get list of metas based on pagination parameters.

parameters.name: $filter
parameters.description: Filters a collection of resources addressed by a request Uniform Resource Locator (URL). Only items for which the expression evaluates to true are included in the response.

parameters.name: $top
parameters.description: Requests the number of items in the queried collection to be included in the result.

parameters.name: count
parameters.description: Get a count of the total records in the collection.

parameters.name: $skip
parameters.description: Specifies the number of items in the queried collection to be skipped and not included in the result.

parameters.name: $select
parameters.description: Selects a subset of properties to include in the response.

parameters.name: asOfDate
parameters.description: Returns records based on the date provided in the request.

parameters.name: asOfDate
parameters.description: Returns records based on the date provided in the request.
